{
  "text": "While CA studies thus reveal what participants are really orienting to, the embodied thinking, feeling, and categorizing subjects with their agendas, experiences, and preferences disappear in CA accounts. This may be desirable from a sociological perspective [CITATION_1] ), yet it fails to account for the processes of categorization to which participants can be shown to attend.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "145480135"
